{"id":59599,"date":"2024-10-07T11:53:00","date_gmt":"2024-10-07T06:23:00","guid":{"rendered":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/?p=59599"},"modified":"2024-10-09T08:02:49","modified_gmt":"2024-10-09T02:32:49","slug":"hinged-vs-sliding-wardrobe-doors-comparison","status":"publish","type":"post","link":"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/hinged-vs-sliding-wardrobe-doors-comparison\/","title":{"rendered":"Wardrobe Sliding Door Vs Hinged Door: Choose Your Style!"},"content":{"rendered":"\n<p>Wardrobe sliding door vs hinged door: Slide or swing? Let&#8217;s settle the debate. Read more here!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Just take a moment and think about it: Do you like the grand reveal of your wardrobe sections every time you open them, or do you prefer the smooth, gliding motion of a <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-interiors\/sliding-door-wardrobe-design\/\">sliding-door wardrobe<\/a>? There might also be days when you are tired of wardrobe doors bumping into your bed or want the traditional feel of a swinging open door.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The wardrobe sliding door vs hinged door debate is a classic challenge every homeowner faces. Such choices are way more than just about considering the aesthetics. The correct wardrobe door also impacts how you move through your space daily. Let&#8217;s break down the pros and cons of sliding wardrobe doors and hinged wardrobe doors to help you make the right choice for your daily routine or maybe even save you from bruises along the way! Read on!<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What are Hinged Wardrobe Doors?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Hinged wardrobe doors, or swing wardrobe doors, have shutters attached to the frame with hinges. Each door opens from its edge and can be single or double, depending on the wardrobe size and design. The wardrobe doors open at a 90-degree angle but can swing wider, depending on the hinge type, giving you easy access to all the sections in one go. The designs are often simple and easy to use and can be seen in most Indian households.\u00a0\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Don&#8217;t miss out on a plethora of wardrobe handle choices that can be easily adapted to different wardrobe patterns, like <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/corner-wardrobe-designs\/\">corner wardrobes<\/a> or fitted designs in rooms with tricky layouts. It is equally important to consider the bedroom dimensions, leg space, and the usability of different sections inside the hinged wardrobe to avoid cramping spaces and comfortable movement inside the room.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075849\/hinged-wardrobe-door-meaning.jpg\" alt=\"Hinged wardrobe doors with swing-open shutters for easy access to wardrobe contents\" class=\"wp-image-59601\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075849\/hinged-wardrobe-door-meaning.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075849\/hinged-wardrobe-door-meaning-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075849\/hinged-wardrobe-door-meaning-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075849\/hinged-wardrobe-door-meaning-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">A timeless design for effortless access<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What are the Pros of Hinged Wardrobe Doors?\u00a0<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Full Access: <\/strong>These wardrobe doors let you open the wardrobe entirely in one go, allowing you to see all its sections.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Easy Maintenance:<\/strong> The doors operate on a simple pull or tilt mechanism of the handle, which makes them easier to maintain or replace when damaged. They don&#8217;t require special fittings.\u00a0\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Easy installation: <\/strong>These doors don&#8217;t demand complex screws or fittings, and the installation process is straightforward.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Fitting Space for Mirrors: <\/strong>Full-length mirrors can be placed on hinged doors, eliminating the need for extra space for a dressing table.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Timeless Design: <\/strong>Hinged wardrobe doors have a traditional look, so they never go out of style. They are also safe to use and offer value for money.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Endless Door Handle Patterns: <\/strong>Changing the door handle can slightly change the look of the wardrobe. Just replace the old handle with one of the countless style options available.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Long Lasting: <\/strong>Since these doors don&#8217;t require any complex screw fittings and are built with durable material, they are long-lasting.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Less Expensive: <\/strong>Hinges are less expensive and readily available than high-quality tracks. <strong>\u00a0<\/strong><\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075909\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-pros.jpg\" alt=\"Hinged wardrobe doors offer full access, easy maintenance, installation, and timeless design with endless handle options\" class=\"wp-image-59603\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075909\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-pros.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075909\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-pros-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075909\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-pros-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075909\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-pros-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Perfect for quick grabs and easy reach<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n<div class=\"mbgc-slide-caption\"><a href=\"#contactUsModal\" data-toggle=\"modal\"><img decoding=\"async\" class=\"img-fluid\" alt=\"Get a Free Modular Kitchen Worth \u20b92 Lakhs with Your Home Interiors.\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2021\/08\/08183703\/designcafe-offer-free-modular-kitchen-worth-2-lakhs.jpg \" \/><\/a><\/div>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What are the Cons of Hinged Wardrobe Doors?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Demand Space: <\/strong>Since the doors swing outwards, you need to ensure enough space around the wardrobe.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Small Room Limitations: <\/strong>These doors are incompatible in rooms with small dimensions.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Can be Inconvenient: <\/strong>Opening each door separately can be difficult sometimes for hinged wardrobes with multiple doors, especially when you are in a hurry.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Less on Modern Appeal:<\/strong> You get limited or traditional designs with hinged wardrobe doors. Sleek and contemporary patterns are few, with not much scope for variety.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Handles can be a Hurdle:<\/strong> In compact rooms, the door handles can create problems because they stick out and entangle in clothes or other items.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Blocking the View: <\/strong>The hinged wardrobe doors might block the view in smaller rooms if left open.\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075900\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-cons.jpg\" alt=\"Cons of hinged wardrobe doors include space demand, traditional designs, handle obstacles, and obstructed view\" class=\"wp-image-59602\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075900\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-cons.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075900\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-cons-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075900\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-cons-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075900\/hinged-wardrobe-doors-cons-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Hinged doors love room to breathe <\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What are Sliding Wardrobe Doors?<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p>Sliding wardrobe doors are a modern alternative to traditional options. They are designed to slide horizontally on the track attached to the wardrobe, granting access to different wardrobe sections and not demanding additional floor space.\u00a0<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>Sliding doors are more popular for large wardrobes or even built-in closets because space efficiency and sleek appearance are equally important. Just slide the doors with minimal effort, and you are good to go!&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075918\/sliding-wardrobe-door-meaning.jpg\" alt=\"Sliding wardrobe doors offer space-saving, modern design with easy access to wardrobe contents\" class=\"wp-image-59604\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075918\/sliding-wardrobe-door-meaning.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075918\/sliding-wardrobe-door-meaning-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075918\/sliding-wardrobe-door-meaning-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075918\/sliding-wardrobe-door-meaning-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Effortless style, one slide at a time!<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What are the Pros of Sliding Wardrobe Doors?<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Space Saving:<\/strong> Since sliding wardrobe doors slide horizontally, they don&#8217;t require any additional space in the room to open.\u00a0\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Tidiness: <\/strong>Wardrobes with sliding doors don&#8217;t require keeping multiple doors open, thus giving a room or space a tidy look.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Aesthetically Pleasing:<\/strong> These doors offer a modern style and look aesthetically pleasing compared to other storage solutions.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Perfect Measurements:<\/strong> Everything in the wardrobe with sliding doors is made according to measurement, so there is nothing to worry about a wardrobe not being the right size for your space.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Storage Solutions:<\/strong> These doors have flexible options for customisation for movements along floors to ceilings. This will multiply your storage space without affecting your <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/home-decor\/home-interior-decor-trends-2024\/\">interior decor<\/a>. Add extra drawers, racks, boxes, shelves, and hanging rails for further functionality and storage boost.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075939\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-pros.jpg\" alt=\"Sliding wardrobe doors pros: space-saving, tidy look, modern design, perfect measurements, and flexible storage\" class=\"wp-image-59606\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075939\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-pros.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075939\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-pros-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075939\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-pros-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075939\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-pros-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Doors that don&#8217;t get in your way<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\">What are the Cons of Sliding Wardrobe Doors?\u00a0<\/h3>\n\n\n\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\">\n<li><strong>Limited View &amp; Access: <\/strong>Sliding wardrobe doors restrict the full inside view of the closet in one go. If one side of the wardrobe is open, the other side is always closed due to the door placement.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Track Maintenance: <\/strong>You need to clean the tracks periodically so that dirt or dust doesn&#8217;t obstruct the smooth movement of the doors.\u00a0<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Installation is Complex: <\/strong>Installing sliding wardrobe doors requires precision and alignment. The process can be more complicated if measurements and fittings don&#8217;t align.<\/li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Expensive:<\/strong> It is important to ensure high-quality fittings and screws to install sliding wardrobe doors so that it doesn&#8217;t obstruct movement. For this, you might have to shell out a little extra, making these doors slightly expensive.\u00a0\u00a0<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n\n\n\n<figure class=\"wp-block-image size-full\"><img decoding=\"async\" width=\"940\" height=\"564\" src=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075929\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-cons.jpg\" alt=\"Cons of Sliding Wardrobe Doors: Limited view &amp; access, track maintenance, complex installation, expensive\" class=\"wp-image-59605\" srcset=\"https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075929\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-cons.jpg 940w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075929\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-cons-300x180.jpg 300w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075929\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-cons-768x461.jpg 768w, https:\/\/media.designcafe.com\/wp-content\/uploads\/2024\/10\/09075929\/sliding-wardrobe-doors-cons-150x90.jpg 150w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 940px) 100vw, 940px\" \/><figcaption class=\"wp-element-caption\">Limited view access but endless design options<\/figcaption><\/figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The decision you have to make between wardrobe sliding doors vs hinged doors depends on your space, style, and preference. Hinged wardrobe doors will give you a classic appeal along with full access. Sliding wardrobe doors, on the other hand, offer sleek, space-saving functionality. Whatever wardrobe door you choose, understanding the pros and cons of each option will aid in making the right choice for your home. Indeed, <a href=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/blog\/bedroom-interiors\/wardrobe-door-design-ideas\/\">wardrobe doors<\/a> could well be the place where functionality meets chic. What&#8217;s more, they say a lot about the design taste of the person who owns them. Talk to the experts at DesignCafe to find the perfect choice for your home.&nbsp;<\/p>\n\n\n\n<h2 class=\"wp-block-heading\">FAQs on Hinged And Sliding Wardrobe Doors<\/h2>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>1. How do wardrobe sliding doors and hinged doors differ in terms of ease of access to the wardrobe contents?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>The main difference in ease of access between wardrobe sliding doors and hinged doors lies in how they open. Hinged doors swing outward, allowing you to open multiple doors simultaneously and giving you full access to the entire wardrobe. This makes it easier to see and reach everything inside simultaneously. On the other hand, sliding doors move horizontally along tracks, meaning you can only access one section of the wardrobe at a time, as one door will always cover part of the wardrobe. While this limits visibility, sliding doors are ideal for tight spaces where outward-swinging doors might be impractical.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p><strong>2. Are there specific cost considerations when opting for sliding doors versus hinged doors for wardrobes?<\/strong><\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>There are some key cost considerations when choosing between sliding and hinged wardrobe doors. Generally, sliding wardrobe doors tend to be more expensive due to the added complexity of the track system and the materials used. Installation can also be more involved, which may increase labour costs. Also, custom-made sliding doors or those with glass or mirrored panels can increase the price.<\/p>\n\n\n\n<p>In contrast, hinged doors are often more affordable, as they have a simpler design and are easier to install. The materials and hardware for hinged doors are typically less costly, and there are fewer moving parts, which can reduce the need for repairs or maintenance over time. However, the final cost will depend on materials, customisation, and the wardrobe size.<\/p>\n\n\n<div class=\"row blog-form\">\n\t<div class=\"offset-lg-3 col-lg-6 bg-light\">\n<fieldset class=\"field-set\">\n<!-- <legend align=\"left\"> -->\n                    \n    <h3 class=\"widget-title text-dark text-center mb-0\">Looking For Functional Interior Designs?<\/h3>\n  \n \n     <p class=\"text-center text-dark mt-0\"> Get 20% extra space with smart solutions<\/p>\n    <!-- <\/legend> -->\n<form id=\"blogContactUsFormMain\" action=\"https:\/\/www.designcafe.com\/get_quote_action.php\" method=\"post\"\n    novalidate=\"novalidate\">\n    <div class=\"form-group\">\n        <input type=\"text\" class=\"form-control\"  name=\"your-name\" placeholder=\"Enter your name*\" \/>\n        <!-- <span class=\"sales-txt-label\" id=\"labeltxt\">Enter your name*<\/span>  -->\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"form-row dc-falg-row\">\n        <!-- <div class=\"form-group col-md-3 guideForm\">\n            <select name=\"your-phon